JOHANNESBURG - Former State Security Minister Ayanda Dlodlo says she doesn't want South Africans feeling unsafe after last year's unrest. She admitted, however, that the department could've done better. READ:Â Violence in SA | Dlodlo confident of vindication Dlodlo was giving evidence at the Human Rights Commission hearing into the July 2021 unrest. She said, "basically why I am sharing this with South Africans because I want to assure South Africans we have hard working individuals in that institution and I wouldn't want South Africans to come out of this thinking they are not safe." "I am trying to illustrate that here was info. Could we have done better? Yes. We did the best that we could at that time and that is all we could do."